  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Development of Local Capacities for Strengthening Primary Health Care Services on Sexual and Reproductive Health, Mental Health, Prevention of Psychoactive Substance Use, Nutritional Health-Phase II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to strengthen local capacities to improve effective access to comprehensive primary health care services, and to design and implement an extramural and intercultural strategy of primary health care. This strategy will promote and provide health services with a gender and equity approach, promoting community and intersectoral action for the construction of scenarios peacekeepers. The strategy will also provide training to 52 peasant or indigenous leaders as public health assistants. Finally, the project will implement a community-based results monitoring system with an intercultural approach. The project will have an emphasis on the exercise of sexual and reproductive rights, mental health, prevention of the consumption of psychoactive substances, attention to children and malnutrition in the 26 municipalities in which the Territorial Training and Reincorporation Spaces-ETCR are located. Additionally, activities are included to support the hospitals and communities affected by the COVID-19 in delivery of personal protection elements for the prevention of contagion of human talent in health, support for the provision of health services and epidemiological surveillance.</narrative>
  </description>
